entries.femaleVariant: We have to talk to HR. We haven't seen our daughter in a month!
Look, we both knew this project would eat up all our time.
And look how we're paying for it! You don't even know if Melody's OK!
Well, I'd rather ask Melody what she had for dinner, not read it in some stupid report. Wouldn't you?
Ah, OK, so now I'm a bad mother?
No! I never said that, you know I didn't... Ehh, never mind.
But her nanny does, and she's sending us detailed reports. Where's the problem?
